#. <section class="sutta" id="sn36.6"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn36.6:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 36"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 36"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn36.6:0.2"
msgid "1. Sagāthāvagga"
msgstr "1. With Verses"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn36.6:0.3"
msgid "6. Sallasutta"
msgstr "6. An Arrow"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi4.208"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
#. VAR: vedayati → vediyati (bj, pts1)
msgctxt "sn36.6:1.1"
msgid ""
"“Assutavā, bhikkhave, puthujjano sukhampi vedanaṃ vedayati, dukkhampi "
"vedanaṃ vedayati, adukkhamasukhampi vedanaṃ vedayati."
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, an uneducated ordinary person feels pleasant, painful, and "
"neutral feelings."

msgctxt "sn36.6:1.2"
msgid ""
"Sutavā, bhikkhave, ariyasāvako sukhampi vedanaṃ vedayati, dukkhampi vedanaṃ "
"vedayati, adukkhamasukhampi vedanaṃ vedayati."
msgstr ""
"An educated noble disciple also feels pleasant, painful, and neutral "
"feelings."

#. VAR: adhippayāso → adhippāyo (bj, mr) | adhippāyaso (s1-3, km) | adhippāyoso (pts1)
msgctxt "sn36.6:1.3"
msgid ""
"Tatra, bhikkhave, ko viseso ko adhippayāso kiṃ nānākaraṇaṃ sutavato "
"ariyasāvakassa assutavatā puthujjanenā”ti?"
msgstr ""
"What, then, is the difference between an ordinary uneducated person and an "
"educated noble disciple?”"

msgctxt "sn36.6:1.4"
msgid "Bhagavaṃmūlakā no, bhante, dhammā … pe …"
msgstr "“Our teachings are rooted in the Buddha. …”"

msgctxt "sn36.6:1.5"
msgid ""
"assutavā, bhikkhave, puthujjano dukkhāya vedanāya phuṭṭho samāno socati "
"kilamati paridevati urattāḷiṃ kandati sammohaṃ āpajjati."
msgstr ""
"“When an uneducated ordinary person experiences painful physical feelings "
"they sorrow and pine and lament, beating their breast and falling into "
"confusion."

msgctxt "sn36.6:1.6"
msgid "So dve vedanā vedayati—"
msgstr "They experience two feelings:"

msgctxt "sn36.6:1.7"
msgid "kāyikañca, cetasikañca."
msgstr "physical and mental."

#. VAR: sallena vijjheyya → sallena vijjheyyuṃ (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "sn36.6:1.8"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, purisaṃ sallena vijjheyya."
msgstr "Suppose a person was struck with an arrow,"

#. VAR: sallena anuvedhaṃ vijjheyya → sallena anuvedhaṃ vijjheyyuṃ (bj, s1-3, km) | sallena vijjheyyuṃ (pts1)
msgctxt "sn36.6:1.9"
msgid "Tamenaṃ dutiyena sallena anuvedhaṃ vijjheyya."
msgstr "only to be struck with a second arrow."

msgctxt "sn36.6:1.10"
msgid "Evañhi so, bhikkhave, puriso dvisallena vedanaṃ vedayati."
msgstr "So that person would experience the feeling of two arrows."

msgctxt "sn36.6:1.11"
msgid ""
"Evameva kho, bhikkhave, assutavā puthujjano dukkhāya vedanāya phuṭṭho samāno "
"socati kilamati paridevati urattāḷiṃ kandati sammohaṃ āpajjati."
msgstr ""
"In the same way, when an uneducated ordinary person experiences painful "
"physical feelings they sorrow and pine and lament, beating their breast and "
"falling into confusion."

msgctxt "sn36.6:1.12"
msgid "So dve vedanā vedayati—"
msgstr "They experience two feelings:"

msgctxt "sn36.6:1.13"
msgid "kāyikañca, cetasikañca."
msgstr "physical and mental."

msgctxt "sn36.6:1.14"
msgid "Tassāyeva kho pana dukkhāya vedanāya phuṭṭho samāno paṭighavā hoti."
msgstr "When they’re touched by painful feeling, they resist it."

msgctxt "sn36.6:1.15"
msgid ""
"Tamenaṃ dukkhāya vedanāya paṭighavantaṃ, yo dukkhāya vedanāya paṭighānusayo, "
"so anuseti."
msgstr ""
"The underlying tendency for repulsion towards painful feeling underlies that."

msgctxt "sn36.6:1.16"
msgid "So dukkhāya vedanāya phuṭṭho samāno kāmasukhaṃ abhinandati."
msgstr ""
"When touched by painful feeling they look forward to enjoying sensual "
"pleasures."

msgctxt "sn36.6:1.17"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu?"
msgstr "Why is that?"

msgctxt "sn36.6:1.18"
msgid ""
"Na hi so, bhikkhave, pajānāti assutavā puthujjano aññatra kāmasukhā dukkhāya "
"vedanāya nissaraṇaṃ, "
msgstr ""
"Because an uneducated ordinary person doesn’t understand any escape from "
"painful feeling apart from sensual pleasures. "

msgctxt "sn36.6:1.19"
msgid ""
"tassa kāmasukhañca abhinandato, yo sukhāya vedanāya rāgānusayo, so anuseti."
msgstr ""
"Since they look forward to enjoying sensual pleasures, the underlying "
"tendency to greed for pleasant feeling underlies that."

msgctxt "sn36.6:1.20"
msgid ""
"So tāsaṃ vedanānaṃ samudayañca atthaṅgamañca assādañca ādīnavañca "
"nissaraṇañca yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti."
msgstr ""
"They don’t truly understand feelings’ origin, ending, gratification, "
"drawback, and escape."

msgctxt "sn36.6:1.21"
msgid ""
"Tassa tāsaṃ vedanānaṃ samudayañca atthaṅgamañca assādañca ādīnavañca "
"nissaraṇañca yathābhūtaṃ appajānato, yo adukkhamasukhāya vedanāya "
"avijjānusayo, so anuseti."
msgstr ""
"The underlying tendency to ignorance about neutral feeling underlies that."

msgctxt "sn36.6:1.22"
msgid "So sukhañce vedanaṃ vedayati, saññutto naṃ vedayati."
msgstr "If they feel a pleasant feeling, they feel it attached."

msgctxt "sn36.6:1.23"
msgid "Dukkhañce vedanaṃ vedayati, saññutto naṃ vedayati."
msgstr "If they feel a painful feeling, they feel it attached."

msgctxt "sn36.6:1.24"
msgid "Adukkhamasukhañce vedanaṃ vedayati, saññutto naṃ vedayati."
msgstr "If they feel a neutral feeling, they feel it attached."

msgctxt "sn36.6:1.25"
msgid ""
"Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, ‘assutavā puthujjano saññutto jātiyā jarāya "
"maraṇena sokehi paridevehi dukkhehi domanassehi upāyāsehi, saññutto "
"dukkhasmā’ti vadāmi."
msgstr ""
"They’re called an uneducated ordinary person who is attached to rebirth, old "
"age, and death, to sorrow, lamentation, pain, sadness, and distress, I say."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn36.6:2.1"
msgid ""
"Sutavā ca kho, bhikkhave, ariyasāvako dukkhāya vedanāya phuṭṭho samāno na "
"socati, na kilamati, na paridevati, na urattāḷiṃ kandati, na sammohaṃ "
"āpajjati."
msgstr ""
"When an educated noble disciple experiences painful physical feelings they "
"don’t sorrow or pine or lament, beating their breast and falling into "
"confusion."

msgctxt "sn36.6:2.2"
msgid "So ekaṃ vedanaṃ vedayati—"
msgstr "They experience one feeling:"

msgctxt "sn36.6:2.3"
msgid "kāyikaṃ, na cetasikaṃ."
msgstr "physical, not mental."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi4.210"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn36.6:3.1"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, purisaṃ sallena vijjheyya."
msgstr "Suppose a person was struck with an arrow,"

msgctxt "sn36.6:3.2"
msgid "Tamenaṃ dutiyena sallena anuvedhaṃ na vijjheyya."
msgstr "and was not struck with a second arrow."

msgctxt "sn36.6:3.3"
msgid "Evañhi so, bhikkhave, puriso ekasallena vedanaṃ vedayati."
msgstr "So that person would experience the feeling of one arrow."

msgctxt "sn36.6:3.4"
msgid ""
"Evameva kho, bhikkhave, sutavā ariyasāvako dukkhāya vedanāya phuṭṭho samāno "
"na socati, na kilamati, na paridevati, na urattāḷiṃ kandati, na sammohaṃ "
"āpajjati."
msgstr ""
"In the same way, when an educated noble disciple experiences painful "
"physical feelings they don’t sorrow or pine or lament, beating their breast "
"and falling into confusion."

msgctxt "sn36.6:3.5"
msgid "So ekaṃ vedanaṃ vedayati—"
msgstr "They experience one feeling:"

msgctxt "sn36.6:3.6"
msgid "kāyikaṃ, na cetasikaṃ."
msgstr "physical, not mental."

msgctxt "sn36.6:3.7"
msgid "Tassāyeva kho pana dukkhāya vedanāya phuṭṭho samāno paṭighavā na hoti."
msgstr "When they’re touched by painful feeling, they don’t resist it."

msgctxt "sn36.6:3.8"
msgid ""
"Tamenaṃ dukkhāya vedanāya appaṭighavantaṃ, yo dukkhāya vedanāya "
"paṭighānusayo, so nānuseti."
msgstr ""
"There’s no underlying tendency for repulsion towards painful feeling "
"underlying that."

msgctxt "sn36.6:3.9"
msgid "So dukkhāya vedanāya phuṭṭho samāno kāmasukhaṃ nābhinandati."
msgstr ""
"When touched by painful feeling they don’t look forward to enjoying sensual "
"pleasures."

msgctxt "sn36.6:3.10"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu?"
msgstr "Why is that?"

msgctxt "sn36.6:3.11"
msgid ""
"Pajānāti hi so, bhikkhave, sutavā ariyasāvako aññatra kāmasukhā dukkhāya "
"vedanāya nissaraṇaṃ."
msgstr ""
"Because an educated noble disciple understands an escape from painful "
"feeling apart from sensual pleasures."

msgctxt "sn36.6:3.12"
msgid ""
"Tassa kāmasukhaṃ nābhinandato yo sukhāya vedanāya rāgānusayo, so nānuseti."
msgstr ""
"Since they don’t look forward to enjoying sensual pleasures, there’s no "
"underlying tendency to greed for pleasant feeling underlying that."

msgctxt "sn36.6:3.13"
msgid ""
"So tāsaṃ vedanānaṃ samudayañca atthaṅgamañca assādañca ādīnavaṃ ca "
"nissaraṇañca yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti."
msgstr ""
"They truly understand feelings’ origin, ending, gratification, drawback, and "
"escape."

msgctxt "sn36.6:3.14"
msgid ""
"Tassa tāsaṃ vedanānaṃ samudayañca atthaṅgamañca assādañca ādīnavañca "
"nissaraṇañca yathābhūtaṃ pajānato, yo adukkhamasukhāya vedanāya "
"avijjānusayo, so nānuseti."
msgstr ""
"There’s no underlying tendency to ignorance about neutral feeling underlying "
"that."

msgctxt "sn36.6:3.15"
msgid "So sukhañce vedanaṃ vedayati, visaññutto naṃ vedayati."
msgstr "If they feel a pleasant feeling, they feel it detached."

msgctxt "sn36.6:3.16"
msgid "Dukkhañce vedanaṃ vedayati, visaññutto naṃ vedayati."
msgstr "If they feel a painful feeling, they feel it detached."

msgctxt "sn36.6:3.17"
msgid "Adukkhamasukhañce vedanaṃ vedayati, visaññutto naṃ vedayati."
msgstr "If they feel a neutral feeling, they feel it detached."

msgctxt "sn36.6:3.18"
msgid ""
"Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, ‘sutavā ariyasāvako visaññutto jātiyā jarāya "
"maraṇena sokehi paridevehi dukkhehi domanassehi upāyāsehi, visaññutto "
"dukkhasmā’ti vadāmi."
msgstr ""
"They’re called an educated noble disciple who is detached from rebirth, old "
"age, and death, from sorrow, lamentation, pain, sadness, and distress, I say."

msgctxt "sn36.6:3.19"
msgid ""
"Ayaṃ kho, bhikkhave, viseso, ayaṃ adhippayāso, idaṃ nānākaraṇaṃ sutavato "
"ariyasāvakassa assutavatā puthujjanenāti."
msgstr ""
"This is the difference between an educated noble disciple and an uneducated "
"ordinary person."

# Text seems to require an implicit “mental” (supplied by BB and Thanissaro) or an idiomatic sense of vedayati as “affected” (Woodward). I follow the latter.
#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn36.6:4.1"
msgid "Na vedanaṃ vedayati sapañño,"
msgstr "A wise and learned person isn’t affected"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn36.6:4.2"
msgid "Sukhampi dukkhampi bahussutopi;"
msgstr "by feelings of pleasure and pain."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn36.6:4.3"
msgid "Ayañca dhīrassa puthujjanena,"
msgstr "This is the great difference in skill"

#. <br>
#. VAR: Mahā → ayaṃ (s1-3, km, mr)
msgctxt "sn36.6:4.4"
msgid "Mahā viseso kusalassa hoti."
msgstr "between the wise and the ordinary."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "sn36.6:5.1"
msgid "Saṅkhātadhammassa bahussutassa,"
msgstr "A learned person who has comprehended the teaching"

#. <br>
#. VAR: Vipassato → sampassato (bj, pts1)
msgctxt "sn36.6:5.2"
msgid "Vipassato lokamimaṃ parañca;"
msgstr "discerns this world and the next."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn36.6:5.3"
msgid "Iṭṭhassa dhammā na mathenti cittaṃ,"
msgstr "Desirable things don’t disturb their mind,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn36.6:5.4"
msgid "Aniṭṭhato no paṭighātameti."
msgstr "nor are they repelled by the undesirable."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "sn36.6:6.1"
msgid "Tassānurodhā athavā virodhā,"
msgstr "Both favoring and opposing"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn36.6:6.2"
msgid "Vidhūpitā atthagatā na santi;"
msgstr "are cleared and ended, they are no more."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn36.6:6.3"
msgid "Padañca ñatvā virajaṃ asokaṃ,"
msgstr "Knowing the stainless, sorrowless state,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn36.6:6.4"
msgid "Sammā pajānāti bhavassa pāragū”ti."
msgstr "they understand rightly, going beyond rebirth.”"

#. </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn36.6:6.5"
msgid "Chaṭṭhaṃ."
msgstr ""
